  "prompt": "When multiple scrum teams are working on the same project, they should make sure each team has different sprint start dates. True or False?",
  "response": "**False.** \n\nWhen multiple Scrum teams are working on the same project, it is generally recommended that they synchronize their sprint start and end dates. This alignment facilitates better collaboration, coordination, and integration among the teams, as they can share updates, discuss dependencies, and align their work more effectively. Having different sprint start dates can lead to confusion and misalignment, making it harder for teams to work together toward the same project goals.",
